at being taken for an eccentric character: “C’est pour les pauvres chiens, for the poor dogs,” he would say (and says so still), “animals are often better than human beings”—an affirmation that provoked (and goes on doing so) passionate disputes, the abbé waxing especially hot. Upon learning that I was a German and a musician the doctor seemed quite fascinated; and from the glances directed at me, I concluded that it was not so much my face (on its way from unshavenness to beardedne